      <Description>Iglesia Pentecostal engages in only one primary program service which is provision of spiritual guidance and education based on principles of the Pentecostal faith. These services are provided through the various prayer services that are offered during the week with the major emphasis on Sunday services. Iglesia Pentecostal has a full time pastor who conducts the various services via a sermon, hymn singing, and other interactive education with the congregation. The church's single biggest expense is the monies paid to the pastor. Iglesia Pentecostal derives its revenues for these program services exclusively through individual support. The church receives no federal, state, local or private corporation grants or other support. The church also derives contributions from deceased member estates through will bequests. During CY2010, the church's program services provided much needed support for the community's poorer population which is facing numerous challenges and adverse conditions owing to the ongoing national recession. Given the qualitative versus quantitative benefits that the church provides, it is difficult to outline specific accomplishments other than to say the congregation and their families receive faith based support</Description>
