      <GeneralExplanation>
        <Explanation>Form 990 is distributed in a preliminary draft form review by the board of directors whose membership ask questions about the proposed filing. The questions are investigated and answered and then any changes needed to be made in the Form 990 are made and a final copy is circulated at which point the Form 990 is prepared for submission to the IRS and the New York State Charities Bureau. The church routinely reviews all contracts and other business transactions for potential conflicts of interest in accordance with the terms of the church's conflict of interest policy. The church makes available its filed Form 1023, 990, conflict of interest policy, whistleblower policy and other related policies available to any contributor or potential contributor by written request. The church, on an annual basis, reviews salary/wage information that is pertinent to church employees working in the vicinity of the church. Comparisions are made by contact with other local chruches and information compiled by Pentecostal faith church councils. Once the information is gathered, the Board of Directors then reviews the findings and makes any adjustments it deems necessary.</Explanation>
